  identifier: ReactiveEvent4
  type: 1
  question:
    sentences:
    - The royal blacksmith offered you the opportunity to forge a new weapon. What
      weapon will you choose?
  answers:
  - identifier: 1
    answerText: 'A sensible and versatile weapon for everyday use: a spear.'
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 1
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 1
      changeValue: 60
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - '<Player> displayed the new spear in every public event. '
      - "The guards were really pleased to have a ruler with such good taste. Even
        guards from other kingdoms enlisted in our guard.\r"
  - identifier: 2
    answerText: 'The weapon that can kill and equally tend the fields: a scythe.'
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 2
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 2
      changeValue: 400
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - '<Player> displayed the new scythe everywhere. '
      - "The commoners were in awe to have such a relatable ruler. Commoners from
        other lands also moved in.\r"
  - identifier: 3
    answerText: A staff. I'll ask the alchemists later to get me a pretty stone that
      fits.
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 4
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 4
      changeValue: 20
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - '<Player> quickly asked the alchemists to make a nice stone for the staff. '
      - "They were happy to give it a beautifully crafted garnet. New alchemists appeared
        from out of nowhere.\r"
  - identifier: 4
    answerText: 'The only real weapon for a ruler: a mighty sword.'
    statChanges:
    - socialClass: 3
      changeValue: 20
    rivalStatChanges: []
    popChanges:
    - socialClass: 3
      changeValue: 40
    resolution:
      sentences:
      - '<Player> displayed the new sword as a real noble. '
      - "The nobles respected even more your royal lineage. Even nobles from other
        kingdoms decided to serve such a radiant heir.\r"
